• **BMI ≥ 40**, or >100 pounds overweight.  
• **BMI ≥ 35** with at least one obesity-related comorbidity (e.g., type 2 diabetes).  
• Failure to achieve sustained weight loss through non-surgical interventions. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}&#8203;:contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

• REE decreases due to loss of fat-free mass (FFM).  
• At 3 months: FM −19 kg, FFM −6 kg → REE −240 kcal/day.  
• At 6 months: FM −20 kg, FFM −8 kg → REE −400 kcal/day. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}&#8203;:contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}

• **Ghrelin:** post‐prandial and diurnal fluctuations are abolished → lower orexigenic drive.  
• **CCK:** restored post‐prandial release to lean levels → enhanced satiety.  
• **GLP-1:** increased post‐meal secretion → improved insulin sensitivity and glucose control. :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}&#8203;:contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}

• Lifelong **micronutrient supplementation** (iron, B12, calcium, vitamin D).  
• Adherence to staged diet progression (liquids → pureed → solids).  
• Regular monitoring for deficiencies and nutritional counseling. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}&#8203;:contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}
